      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — Task 91: Resolve {ROLE}/{ROLE_INSTRUCTIONS} placeholders in SYNAPSE.md\n\n## Finding\n`buildSystemPrompt()` in `src/index.ts` already performed harness injection at spawn time. The only gap was `GET /api/agents/:id/prompt` in `src/dashboard.ts`, which read raw `.synapse/SYNAPSE.md` (with unresolved placeholders) instead of calling the resolver.\n\n## Changes (commit d57e9b8 on branch synapse/developer-role-injection)\n\n- **src/system-prompt.ts** (new): Extracted `buildSystemPrompt(role)` into a shared module. Reads `templates/SYNAPSE.md`, substitutes `{ROLE}` and `{ROLE_INSTRUCTIONS}` based on role, returns the fully resolved string.\n- **src/index.ts**: Now imports `buildSystemPrompt` from `./system-prompt.js`. Replaced local `parseRoleMeta` with `parseRoleFile` from `./roles.js` (equivalent, already existed).\n- **src/dashboard.ts**: `GET /api/agents/:id/prompt` now calls `buildSystemPrompt(role)` and returns `resolved_prompt` (fully substituted) instead of raw `base_protocol` + `slot_doc` + `role_body` fragments. Falls back to inferring role from slot if agent.role is null.\n- **public/index.html**: Prompt modal simplified from 4 sections (base protocol, role-specific protocol, role instructions, boot task) to 2 (system prompt, boot task).\n- **public/app.js**: Updated `openPromptModal` to render `data.resolved_prompt` in the single \"System prompt\" section.\n\n## Build/test\nTypeScript build passes (`npm run build` with zero errors).",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780904618663,
